<h1>Yamaha Music Education Centre Terms of Enrolment</h1>

<ol>
	<li>A deposit of $50 is payable with this enrolment and will be deducted from the first invoice. This is a non-refundable deposit.</li>
	<li>Fees are payable on school term in advance on receipt of invoice. Books and kits are an expense additional to fees and must be paid for as requested by the school.</li>
	<li>Fees will not be refunded for lessons not attended, however, leave of absence may be granted if your child is unable to attend for four (4) or more consecutive lessons.</li>
	<li>Should you wish to discontinue the Yamaha course, we request you provide a minimum of four weeks written notice to the school office otherwise four (4) weeks fees will be payable in lieu.</li>
	<li>Siblings are not permitted in the classroom, since they may prove to be a distraction to other students.</li>
	<li>New classes will not begin until there is a minimum of six (6) paid deposits. This may be up to four weeks into the new term. You will receive a ltter in the week your class is due to start to confirm the date of the first lesson.</li>
	<li>We endeavour to maintain the class day, time, location and teacher for the duration of the course. If unforseen circumstances arise, such as a class falling below four students, or a teacher becomes unavailable, there may be a need to change the day, time, location and/or teacher.</li>
</ol>




